.cache/

# ========================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ========================================
# 
# Files that ARE safe to commit:
# ✅ .env.example (template with placeholder values)
# ✅ .env.template (template with placeholder values)
# ✅ .env.local.example (template with placeholder values)
# ✅ firebase.json (public Firebase config)
# ✅ .firebaserc (public Firebase config)
# ✅ firestore.rules (security rules - no secrets)
# ✅ firestore.indexes.json (indexes - no secrets)
# ✅ next.config.js (config file - uses env vars, no hardcoded secrets)
# ✅ All .md documentation files
# 
# Files that should NEVER be committed:
# ❌ .env.local (contains REAL API keys)
# ❌ .env (contains REAL API keys)
# ❌ Any *-service-account*.json files
# ❌ Any files with "private-key" in the name
# ❌ Any files with actual API tokens/secrets
*.tsbuildinfo
